Package: DROP
Type: Package
Title: Distributionally Robust Optimization for Precision Matrices
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Canruo", "Shen", email = "canruo.shen@ubc.ca", 
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Implements adaptive distributionally robust optimization (DROP) for 
    estimating high-dimensional Gaussian graphical models. The method achieves 
    robust graph recovery through a rank-based inverse normal transformation 
    and efficiently solves the adaptive-weighted objective function using a 
    coordinate descent algorithm with C++ acceleration and parallel computing 
    for improved performance.
